Look at what the teams did without the players and look at what the players did without their teams. Montana made it to maybe one AFC title game after leaving the 49ers, while his old team won the superbowl without him. I think it's fair to say that is system. Farve did well with Greenbay and the Vikings. I wouldn't consider that system. Manning made the colts into something, then they had to completely rebuild because they were trash without him, then he went to Denver and they instantly became superbowl contenders and won their division every year. People talk about the d# carrying him to 50, maybe it did, but what have they done since he's been gone? Missed the playoffs twice and finished last in their division this year. Manning also went to 4 superbowls with 4 different coaches, there's no way he's a system qb. As for the others you mentioned, I don't know much about them, but Brady and Montana thus far fit the bill of system qb. Manning and Farve, not so much.
